TY  - JOUR
T1  - Supply, Storage, and Service Reliability Decisions by Gas Distribution Utilities: A Chance-Constrained Approach: Comments on Guldmann's Paper
AU  - Rasmussen, Jill J.
Y1  - 1983/08/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.8.907
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.8.907
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 907
EP  - 908
VL  - 29
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A question has been raised as to the value of Guldmann's paper because the model application indicates very small increments of benefits over costs for the ?optimal? decision across a wide range of ?nonoptimal? ones. That is, no matter what decision is made about storage capacity or reliability level, savings are on the order of 1 percent of costs. In addition, similar increments of benefit occur irrespective of conversion capacity or reliability level.
